==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|wid|wīd|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|wīdaz|lang=en}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|wijd|lang=nl}}, German {{term|weit|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|vid|lang=sv}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/waɪd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-wide.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{audio|En-uk-wide.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪd}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|wid|er}}

# Having a large physical extent from side to side.
#: ''We walked down a '''wide''' corridor.''
# Large in scope.
#: ''The inquiry had a '''wide''' remit.''
# {{sports}} Operating at the side of the playing area.
#: ''That team needs a decent '''wide''' player.''

